<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="763" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="55.[718,1311,3008,3426]" lastBlockId="55.[108,1309,3440,3465]" pageId="55" pageNumber="763">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[719,999,3156,3189]" pageId="55" pageNumber="763">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 230-280 mm, tail 230-250 mm; weight c.388 g. Hairs on dorsal surface of head and back of Hagen’s Flying Squirrel are slate-colored, with reddish brown tips. Band of blacktipped hairs runs from middle of nose, around eyes, to ears. There are stiff long hairs in front of and behind ears. Hairs on gliding membranes are black, with reddish
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[1374,2582,279,910]" pageId="55" pageNumber="763">brown tips. Underparts are white, with reddish tint. Tail is thickly haired; upper parts of tail are brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
